ir contributions. The volume includes chapters investigating fluency from an L2 perspective and integrates perspectives from related fields, such as psycholinguistics, sign language studies and L2 assessment. The book extends the common foci and approaches of fluency studies and offers new perspectives that enable readers to evaluate critically existing paradigms and models. This encourages the development of more comprehensive frameworks and directs future L2 fluency research into new areas of L2 learning and use.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aFluency (Language learning) 0aFluency (Language learning). 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teaching. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 assessment.  aL2 fluency.  aL2 pedagogy.  aL2 use .  aSLA .  afluency in language learning and use.  afluency.  alanguage use.  alistening skills.  areading skills.  asecond language acquisition.  asecond language assessment.  asecond language learning and use.  asecond language learning.  asecond language teaching.  aspeaking skills.  awriting skills.1 aAlisaari, Jenni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnckar, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaapanen, Ulla-Maija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeikkola, Leena Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuhta, Ari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHynninen, Niina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKallio, Heini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanto, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLintunen, Pekka, econtributor